## 🧭 3-Step Setup

:column[size:3](#quickstart-columns)

### 🛠  
### 1. Download + Unpack

Pick your platform:

- 🪟 [Windows](https://github.com/bitboyb/Slamhaus/releases/download/nightly/slamhaus-windows.zip)  
- 🐧 [Debian/Ubuntu](https://github.com/bitboyb/Slamhaus/releases/download/nightly/slamhaus-linux-debian.zip)  
- 🎩 [Arch Linux](https://github.com/bitboyb/Slamhaus/releases/download/nightly/slamhaus-linux-arch.zip)

Unzip it. 

#### On Linux:

```
chmod +x slamhaus
```

:column[]()

### 📁

### 2. Add a `content/` Folder

Put your Markdown files and media into a folder like this:

```text
your-project/
├── slamhaus
└── content/
    ├── index.slam
    └── include/
        └── nav.smd
```

Use the [Basic Template](https://github.com/bitboyb/Slamhaus-Basic-Template) to get started instantly.

:column[]()

### ▶️

### 3. Build + View

Build your site:

```bash
./slamhaus
```

Your static site is now in the `output/` folder.
Open `index.html` in any browser or host with a local server.

:/column

